      "from_id": "cec50b17:3",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — worktree merge auto-attaches commit_sha by slot\n\n**Files changed:**\n- `src/db.ts` (+21): new `attachCommitToActivityBySlot(slot, commitSha)` — resolves slot→agent_id via `getAgentBySlot`, then updates the most recent `in_progress` activity with `commit_sha IS NULL` for that agent. Returns false if slot has no agent or no matching activity.\n- `src/index.ts` (+27/-2): added import of `attachCommitToActivityBySlot`; added `slotFromSlug(name)` and `attachMergeCommit(root, name)` helpers; wired `attachMergeCommit` into both the ff-only and squash merge success paths, before the prune step.\n\n**Build:** `bun run build` → clean\n\n**Regex:** `/^[a-z-]+?-(\\d+)(?:-|$)/` — the lazy `+?` on `[a-z-]+` expands just enough to consume the role (including hyphens in names like `code-reviewer`), then matches `-<digits>` followed by either a hyphen or end-of-string. Tested against `developer-19-foo` → 19, `code-reviewer-19-foo` → 19, `developer-3` → 3, `code-reviewer-3` → 3. ✓\n\n**Error handling:**\n- Regex miss (unparseable slug): logs a warning to stderr, skips attach, merge continues.\n- Slot has no agent (`getAgentBySlot` returns null): `attachCommitToActivityBySlot` returns false silently.\n- No in_progress activity for that agent: SQL UPDATE changes=0, returns false silently.\n- Any exception (DB error, git rev-parse failure): caught, logged to stderr, merge continues.",
      "priority": 5,
